<br>
Im a bub from 25 and near completion of current quest. Almost the entire game has been solo for me (not completely by choice), so Ive focused on specific targets/drops. Im hoping others will suggest mobs that need eliminating (repeatedly!), and possible mobs for future targeting.<br>
<br>
 I have not yet been to Kunark, so thats completly foreign and unsecure terrain for me. Id like to be around 30th before I go there. Like I said, I solo...<br>
<br>
 Ive done the hermit, but not strong enough to fend off the Tesch Mas...<br>
 The Eyes in Xxorb(?) are green...<br>
<br>
 suggestions please?   thanks much, Yaht <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 2:00:51 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> First stop...</span><hr size=1> If you area heading to kunark at that level, the first stop should be Lake of Ill Omen.  Even though it is usually packed, there are usually pleanty of mobs to keep you busy.  Sabertooth Grimalkins, Goblin Warlords, Sarnaks, etc.  May wanna try.  Just be ready for a decent amount of medding.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unucle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nucle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/14/01 4:15:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: First stop...</span><hr size=1> Hmmm, 25 to 29 is tough to solo, at 29 the real fun starts with BoF. There is a single aviak spawn in lake rathetear you could proly camp for a couple levels, it is crowded but good work if you can get it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Xp is pretty good, but you should really find a partner or group in North Karana,  Aviaks there give excellent XP at your level... Lake of Ill omen is also an excellent choice... <p><IMG 
